Key Match Events: Merih Demiral scored once in each half, including the first goal after just 57 seconds.
Both of Turkey's goals came from corner kicks, both whipped in by Arda Guler.
Michael Gregoritsch scored for Austria in the 66th minute from a corner kick.
Turkey's goalkeeper Mert Gunok made a crucial save in the final minute of added time.
Post-Match Reflections: Ronald Koeman says Netherlands cannot afford to drop ‘level’ after their ‘outstanding’ display against Romania.
Turkey will now face the Netherlands in Berlin in the quarter-finals.
Vincenzo Montella's side has a chance to go further than any Turkish side before them in a major tournament.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Arda Guler orchestrated everything good that Turkey did and drew fouls to alleviate the pressure on his side.
Player ratings: Merih Demiral, Arda Guler, and Mert Gunok received the highest scores.
